WEBVTT

1
00:00:01.368 --> 00:00:02.779
<i>TENZIN: Earth.</i>

2
00:00:03.303 --> 00:00:04.646
<i>Fire.</i>

3
00:00:04.972 --> 00:00:06.349
<i>Air.</i>

4
00:00:06.840 --> 00:00:08.046
Water.

5
00:00:08.842 --> 00:00:12.881
<i>Only the Avatar can master
all four elements</i>

6
00:00:12.980 --> 00:00:15.187
<i>and bring balance to the world.</i>

7
00:00:20.854 --> 00:00:24.063
<i>NARRATOR: Republic City welcomes
a new citizen into her arms.</i>

8
00:00:24.191 --> 00:00:25.898
<i>Avatar Korra!</i>

9
00:00:25.993 --> 00:00:29.634
<i>After years of seclusion in the South
this master of water. earth and fire</i>

10
00:00:29.696 --> 00:00:32.404
<i>seeks to add airbending
to her list of skills.</i>

11
00:00:32.499 --> 00:00:36.003
<i>And under the tutelage of Tenzin.
Avatar Aang's son. she should go far.</i>

12
00:00:36.503 --> 00:00:39.006
<i>But will this cool. calm.
collected master of air</i>

13
00:00:39.006 --> 00:00:40.917
<i>be able to tame this hot-headed teen?</i>

14
00:00:46.713 --> 00:00:48.090
(GRUNTING)

15
00:00:50.384 --> 00:00:52.022
KORRA: (READING)
And in the final round.

16
00:00:52.019 --> 00:00:53.225
"the Buzzard Wasps won.

17
00:00:53.320 --> 00:00:55.493
"with a decisive knockout."

18
00:00:55.556 --> 00:00:57.001
What do you say
we go to the arena tonight?

19
00:00:57.057 --> 00:00:59.094
Catch a few Pro-bending matches?

20
00:00:59.393 --> 00:01:02.931
That "sport" is a mockery of
the noble tradition of bending.

21
00:01:03.030 --> 00:01:04.600
Come on. Tenzin.

22
00:01:04.698 --> 00:01:07.042
I've dreamed about seeing
a Pro-bending match since I was a kid.

23
00:01:07.034 --> 00:01:09.241
and now I'm just a ferry ride away
from the arena.

24
00:01:09.336 --> 00:01:11.612
Korra. you're not here
to watch that drivel.

25
00:01:11.705 --> 00:01:13.878
You're here to finish your Avatar training.

26
00:01:14.041 --> 00:01:16.920
So. for the time being.
I want you to remain on the island.

27
00:01:17.010 --> 00:01:19.047
Is that why you're keeping
the White Lotus sentries around.

28
00:01:19.046 --> 00:01:21.117
-to watch my every move?
- Yes.

29
00:01:21.214 --> 00:01:25.754
In order to learn airbending. I believe
you require a calm. quiet environment.

30
00:01:25.852 --> 00:01:27.525
free from any distractions.

31
00:01:27.588 --> 00:01:29.932
All right. you're the master.

32
00:01:38.198 --> 00:01:42.374
So my mother informed me that you've
never been able to airbend before.

33
00:01:42.769 --> 00:01:43.873
(KORRA SIGHS)

34
00:01:44.071 --> 00:01:45.607
Yeah. but I don't know why.

35
00:01:45.706 --> 00:01:47.652
The other elements came
so easily to me.

36
00:01:47.741 --> 00:01:50.984
But every single time
I've tried airbending...

37
00:01:51.078 --> 00:01:52.079
(BLOWS RASPBERRIES) Nothing.

38
00:01:52.279 --> 00:01:54.885
That's perfectly all right.
we just need to be patient.

39
00:01:55.082 --> 00:01:58.086
Often. the element that's the most
difficult for the Avatar to master

40
00:01:58.085 --> 00:02:01.066
is the one most opposite
to the Avatar's personality.

41
00:02:01.121 --> 00:02:02.998
For Aang. it was earthbending.

42
00:02:03.090 --> 00:02:06.299
Yeah. well. I'm about as opposite
an Airbender as you can get.

43
00:02:06.560 --> 00:02:08.836
Let's begin your first lesson.

44
00:02:11.298 --> 00:02:14.108
Korra's going to airbend!
Korra's going to airbend!

45
00:02:14.101 --> 00:02:15.842
KORRA: What is that contraption?

46
00:02:15.936 --> 00:02:20.681
A time honored tool that teaches the
most fundamental aspect of airbending.

47
00:02:20.774 --> 00:02:23.118
Jinora. would you like to
explain this exercise?

48
00:02:23.176 --> 00:02:25.247
The goal is to weave your way
through the gates

49
00:02:25.312 --> 00:02:28.122
and make it to the other side
without touching them.

50
00:02:28.348 --> 00:02:29.656
Seems easy enough.

51
00:02:29.750 --> 00:02:32.629
Jinora forgot to say you have to make it
through while the gates are spinning.

52
00:02:42.129 --> 00:02:44.973
TENZIN: The key is to be like the leaf.

53
00:02:47.000 --> 00:02:50.140
Flow with the movement of the gates.

54
00:02:51.705 --> 00:02:53.207
Jinora will demonstrate.

55
00:02:55.509 --> 00:02:58.456
Airbending is all about
spiral movements.

56
00:02:58.512 --> 00:03:00.048
When you meet resistance.

57
00:03:00.147 --> 00:03:03.458
you must be able to switch direction
at a moment's notice.

58
00:03:10.323 --> 00:03:11.961
Let's do this.

59
00:03:12.559 --> 00:03:14.038
-(CRASH)
-(GRUNTING)

60
00:03:18.031 --> 00:03:19.374
(GRUNTING REPEATEDLY)

61
00:03:21.168 --> 00:03:22.238
(GROANING)

62
00:03:28.175 --> 00:03:29.882
Don't force your way through.

63
00:03:31.011 --> 00:03:32.649
Dance! Dance like the wind!

64
00:03:33.580 --> 00:03:35.150
Be the leaf!

65
00:03:36.583 --> 00:03:37.584
(GRUNTING)

66
00:03:41.555 --> 00:03:42.727
(SIGHS)

67
00:03:47.527 --> 00:03:49.006
Airbend!

68
00:03:51.665 --> 00:03:53.576
What is wrong with me?

69
00:03:53.867 --> 00:03:54.868
Airbend!

70
00:03:55.202 --> 00:03:56.203
(GROANING)

71
00:04:00.240 --> 00:04:01.241
Ugh!

72
00:04:01.608 --> 00:04:04.214
Maybe I'm just not cut out
to be an Airbender. huh. Naga?

73
00:04:04.344 --> 00:04:05.687
<i>SHIRO: (OVER RADIO) Ladies
and gentlemen.</i>

74
00:04:05.779 --> 00:04:08.726
<i>I'm coming to you live
from Republic City's Pro-bending Arena.</i>

75
00:04:08.882 --> 00:04:11.556
<i>where tonight. the best in the world
continue their quest</i>

76
00:04:11.618 --> 00:04:14.895
<i>for a spot in the upcoming
Championship Tournament.</i>

77
00:04:14.955 --> 00:04:16.798
<i>Grab your snacks and grab your kids.</i>

78
00:04:16.890 --> 00:04:20.235
<i>because this next match
is going to be a doozy.</i>

79
00:04:20.594 --> 00:04:22.232
<i>This Mako's got moxie!</i>

80
00:04:22.229 --> 00:04:24.266
<i>He advances. fires two quick shots.</i>

81
00:04:24.364 --> 00:04:26.207
<i>Yomo is hammered back to Zone 3.</i>

82
00:04:26.266 --> 00:04:28.610
<i>The clock is winding down.
can Yomo hold on?</i>

83
00:04:28.702 --> 00:04:30.409
He's teetering on the edge
of the ring now.

84
00:04:30.470 --> 00:04:32.416
<i>The Fire Ferrets line up to strike...</i>

85
00:04:35.776 --> 00:04:37.255
Korra. come down here. please.

86
00:04:40.080 --> 00:04:41.718
You shut it off at the best part!

87
00:04:41.782 --> 00:04:43.625
I thought I made myself clear.

88
00:04:43.717 --> 00:04:47.062
I don't want you listening
to this distracting nonsense.

89
00:04:47.120 --> 00:04:48.394
But it's their radio!

90
00:04:48.455 --> 00:04:51.265
And. technically. you said
I couldn't watch a match.

91
00:04:51.258 --> 00:04:53.260
you didn't say anything
about listening to one.

92
00:04:53.326 --> 00:04:54.828
You... (GROANS)

93
00:04:54.928 --> 00:04:56.430
You know what I meant.

94
00:04:56.496 --> 00:04:57.804
Anyway. shouldn't you...

95
00:04:57.898 --> 00:04:59.969
Shouldn't you be in bed by now'?

96
00:05:10.677 --> 00:05:12.418
(SNIFFING)

97
00:05:18.285 --> 00:05:19.628
I think I'm doing it wrong.

98
00:05:19.920 --> 00:05:21.365
There's nothing to do.

99
00:05:21.454 --> 00:05:23.525
Let your mind and your spirit be free.

100
00:05:23.623 --> 00:05:25.830
for air is the element of freedom.

101
00:05:25.926 --> 00:05:27.872
(SCOFFS AND LAUGHS)

102
00:05:28.495 --> 00:05:30.099
ls something funny?

103
00:05:30.163 --> 00:05:32.200
Yeah. you're telling me
to embrace freedom.

104
00:05:32.299 --> 00:05:34.677
but you won't even let me
listen to the radio?

105
00:05:34.768 --> 00:05:36.975
And forget about leaving this island.

106
00:05:37.204 --> 00:05:39.616
Please. Korra. Look at Meelo.

107
00:05:39.673 --> 00:05:41.482
He's able to meditate peacefully.

108
00:05:42.309 --> 00:05:44.289
(SNORING)

109
00:05:45.045 --> 00:05:47.821
- Actually. I think he's asleep.
- What?

110
00:05:47.881 --> 00:05:50.327
Well. at least he has
the relaxing part down.

111
00:05:50.450 --> 00:05:53.897
Whatever. None of this airbending stuff
makes any sense to me.

112
00:05:53.987 --> 00:05:57.696
I know you're frustrated. but
these teachings will sink in over time.

113
00:05:57.791 --> 00:06:00.362
Then one day. they'll just click.

114
00:06:00.827 --> 00:06:02.329
(KORRA INHALES)

115
00:06:03.964 --> 00:06:06.001
Yeah. it's not sinking in yet.

116
00:06:06.066 --> 00:06:07.670
I'm going to go get a glass
of lychee juice.

117
00:06:07.734 --> 00:06:09.975
Korra. the meditation's not over yet.

118
00:06:10.637 --> 00:06:12.412
Daddy. can I have
some lychee juice. too?

119
00:06:12.505 --> 00:06:13.540
No.

120
00:06:14.307 --> 00:06:15.342
(MEELO GROANING)

121
00:06:59.119 --> 00:07:00.291
(GASPING)

122
00:07:25.211 --> 00:07:27.555
Hey. what are you doing in my gym?

123
00:07:28.148 --> 00:07:30.890
Uh. I was just looking for a bathroom
and I got lost.

124
00:07:30.951 --> 00:07:33.431
Ah. the old "I-had-to-pee" excuse.

125
00:07:33.420 --> 00:07:36.424
You know. I'm sick and tired of you kids
sneaking in without paying.

126
00:07:36.423 --> 00:07:37.993
I'm taking you to security.

127
00:07:38.091 --> 00:07:40.332
- No. wait...
- There you are!

128
00:07:40.427 --> 00:07:42.304
I've been looking everywhere for you.

129
00:07:42.429 --> 00:07:43.737
It's all right. Toza.

130
00:07:43.997 --> 00:07:45.977
- She's with me.
- Yeah. I'm with him.

131
00:07:46.066 --> 00:07:47.670
So. you see. we're together.

132
00:07:47.767 --> 00:07:49.940
Well. not “together” together.
More like friends.

133
00:07:50.003 --> 00:07:52.074
Right. friends.
No. no. I didn't mean to imply...

134
00:07:52.138 --> 00:07:53.139
-(CLEARS THROAT)
- Oh. you implied it.

135
00:07:53.440 --> 00:07:56.444
I don't care what you are.
I've got work to do.

136
00:07:57.911 --> 00:08:00.448
Right this way. miss.

137
00:08:00.447 --> 00:08:01.858
Thank you. sir.

138
00:08:02.615 --> 00:08:04.458
Seriously. thanks!

139
00:08:06.987 --> 00:08:09.866
What do you think?
Best seats in the house. huh?

140
00:08:10.457 --> 00:08:12.869
KORRA: Whoa. unbelievable!

141
00:08:14.127 --> 00:08:16.869
This place is even more amazing
than I imagined!

142
00:08:16.997 --> 00:08:19.477
- Name's Bolin. by the way.
- Korra.

143
00:08:19.666 --> 00:08:20.701
MAI-(O: Psst.

144
00:08:20.800 --> 00:08:22.677
- Bolin.
- Yeah?

145
00:08:23.036 --> 00:08:26.483
I told you. you have to stop bringing
your crazy fan girls in here

146
00:08:26.473 --> 00:08:28.680
before the matches. Get her out of here.

147
00:08:29.042 --> 00:08:31.352
Aww. come on. Mako.

148
00:08:31.611 --> 00:08:34.387
All right. look. I kind of promised her
she could stay.

149
00:08:34.481 --> 00:08:37.485
But. man. I got a good feeling.
There's something special about her.

150
00:08:37.484 --> 00:08:39.122
I know it. Come here.

151
00:08:39.185 --> 00:08:41.495
I want you to meet my brother. Mako.

152
00:08:41.488 --> 00:08:42.694
Make?

153
00:08:42.789 --> 00:08:44.860
Wow. I heard you play on the radio...

154
00:08:44.958 --> 00:08:46.960
Come on. Bolin. we're up.

155
00:08:47.027 --> 00:08:48.904
Or I could meet him later.

156
00:08:49.062 --> 00:08:50.507
Yeah. sorry about that.

157
00:08:50.497 --> 00:08:53.706
My brother just gets real focused
before a match.

158
00:08:53.800 --> 00:08:55.507
Okay. I got to go!

159
00:08:55.502 --> 00:08:58.506
Wish me luck. Not that I'll need it.

160
00:08:58.972 --> 00:09:01.543
KORRA: (CHUCKLES)
Good luck! Knock 'em out!

161
00:09:07.347 --> 00:09:11.818
<i>Introducing the Fire Ferrets!</i>

162
00:09:12.519 --> 00:09:14.863
FAN: (SCREAMS) I love you. Bolin!

163
00:09:15.255 --> 00:09:17.667
<i>The rookie Ferrets came
from out of nowhere</i>

164
00:09:17.724 --> 00:09:19.829
<i>and have made it further than
anyone expected this season.</i>

165
00:09:19.893 --> 00:09:22.703
<i>But tonight they face
their toughest test yet. folks.</i>

166
00:09:24.998 --> 00:09:25.999
(DINGS)

167
00:09:26.066 --> 00:09:27.067
<i>And they're off!</i>

168
00:09:27.167 --> 00:09:31.081
<i>The two teams waste no time trying to
blast each other out of Zone 1.</i>

169
00:09:33.673 --> 00:09:36.677
<i>Hasook is the first
to feel the heat of the Tigerdillos.</i>

170
00:09:36.776 --> 00:09:39.723
<i>He tries to return the favor.
but they're too fast for him.</i>

171
00:09:39.779 --> 00:09:43.522
<i>while Mako showcases his trademark
"cool under fire " style.</i>

172
00:09:44.517 --> 00:09:46.360
-(GRUNTING)
-(BUZZER SOUNDS)

173
00:09:46.419 --> 00:09:49.696
<i>The Tigerdillos score with a walloping
one-two combo.</i>

174
00:09:50.590 --> 00:09:53.594
<i>Can their teammate hold on
to their Zone 1 territory?</i>

175
00:09:56.196 --> 00:09:57.197
(BUZZER SOUNDS)

176
00:09:57.530 --> 00:09:59.908
<i>Guess not! Mako's over the line.</i>

177
00:09:59.966 --> 00:10:02.810
<i>The Tigentillos get the green light
and advance into Ferret territory.</i>

178
00:10:03.303 --> 00:10:04.748
Come on. Ferrets!

179
00:10:07.941 --> 00:10:09.614
<i>- Looks like Hasook's in trouble.
-(BUZZER SOUNDS)</i>

180
00:10:09.709 --> 00:10:11.985
<i>He's in Zone 3. teetering over the brink!</i>

181
00:10:13.246 --> 00:10:14.589
(YELLING)

182
00:10:15.115 --> 00:10:18.460
<i>And Hasook takes a dip!
He'll be back for Round 2.</i>

183
00:10:18.551 --> 00:10:19.894
<i>assuming the fabulous bending brothers</i>

184
00:10:19.953 --> 00:10:21.728
<i>can hold their ground
until the next round.</i>

185
00:10:22.589 --> 00:10:24.330
-(BUZZER SOUNDS)
-(BELL RINGS)

186
00:10:24.591 --> 00:10:30.234
<i>RING ANNOUNCER: Round 1 goes to
the Golden Temple Tigerdillosl</i>

187
00:10:30.597 --> 00:10:32.599
Come on. Hasook. get your act together.

188
00:10:33.500 --> 00:10:34.501
(DINGS)

189
00:10:36.336 --> 00:10:37.337
(BUZZER SOUNDS)

190
00:10:37.504 --> 00:10:39.074
SHIRO: The Fire Ferrets
are knocked into Zone 2

191
00:10:39.139 --> 00:10:40.914
<i>and the Tigerdillos advance.</i>

192
00:10:50.650 --> 00:10:51.822
(BUZZER SOUNDS)

193
00:10:55.622 --> 00:10:56.623
(BUZZER SOUNDS)

194
00:10:57.357 --> 00:10:58.427
(BELL RINGS)

195
00:10:58.491 --> 00:11:01.495
<i>The Fire Ferrets cinch the round
in the closing seconds.</i>

196
00:11:01.594 --> 00:11:02.629
<i>It's one apiece.</i>

197
00:11:02.629 --> 00:11:05.200
<i>Still anyone's match
as we go into the third and final round.</i>

198
00:11:05.298 --> 00:11:06.299
(BELL muss)

199
00:11:08.468 --> 00:11:12.473
<i>Hasook stumbles and now he tumbles.
right into his teammate.</i>

200
00:11:12.539 --> 00:11:15.349
<i>He and Bolin better untangle quick
if they don't want to...</i>

201
00:11:15.441 --> 00:11:16.681
-(BUZZER SOUNDS)
- Oh. too late!

202
00:11:17.644 --> 00:11:18.782
Oh. no!

203
00:11:19.045 --> 00:11:20.786
<i>SHIRO: It's all up to Mako now.</i>

204
00:11:20.847 --> 00:11:23.657
<i>He's bobbing and weaving.
He's weaving and bobbing.</i>

205
00:11:23.650 --> 00:11:25.152
<i>But he's not hitting back.</i>

206
00:11:25.218 --> 00:11:29.166
<i>If Mako's knocked out.
the Ferrets' fabulous season is over.</i>

207
00:11:29.889 --> 00:11:33.701
<i>He's dancing on the edge of the ring.
surviving the three-on-one barrage.</i>

208
00:11:33.793 --> 00:11:37.206
<i>It seems his plan is to let
the Tigerdillos punch themselves out.</i>

209
00:11:37.297 --> 00:11:39.243
<i>- And his plan is working!
-(BUZZER SOUNDS)</i>

210
00:11:39.332 --> 00:11:40.504
<i>Hahn is in the pool.</i>

211
00:11:40.567 --> 00:11:44.379
<i>They've got nothing left in the tank.
and Mako is on the offensive!</i>

212
00:11:45.371 --> 00:11:46.679
It's two-on-one.

213
00:11:46.673 --> 00:11:48.380
- Scratch that. It's one-on-one.
-(BUZZER SOUNDS)

214
00:11:48.474 --> 00:11:51.512
<i>And it's an earth and fire slugfest!</i>

215
00:11:51.878 --> 00:11:53.585
<i>There's so much smoke and dust
from the fire fight...</i>

216
00:11:53.680 --> 00:11:54.681
(BUZZER SOUNDS)

217
00:11:54.681 --> 00:11:56.683
<i>...I can't even see
where the Fire Ferret is!</i>

218
00:12:00.653 --> 00:12:02.030
-(CROWD CHEERING)
- It's a knockout!

219
00:12:02.088 --> 00:12:04.534
<i>-(BELL RINGS)
- What a wing-dinger of a hat trick. folks!</i>

220
00:12:04.591 --> 00:12:08.562
<i>Mako pulls off the upset of the season.
winning the match for the Fire Ferrets!</i>

221
00:12:17.503 --> 00:12:18.846
Wahoo! Yes!

222
00:12:19.239 --> 00:12:22.948
One more win and
we're in the Championship Tournament.

223
00:12:23.843 --> 00:12:26.255
So what did you think. Korra?

224
00:12:26.346 --> 00:12:28.292
Bolin's got some moves. huh?

225
00:12:28.448 --> 00:12:30.928
What did I think? What did I think?

226
00:12:31.017 --> 00:12:32.621
That was amazing.

227
00:12:32.719 --> 00:12:36.428
You did more harm than good out there.
You almost cost us the match.

228
00:12:36.556 --> 00:12:38.126
- We won. didn't we?
- Barely.

229
00:12:38.224 --> 00:12:39.726
Get off my case. pal!

230
00:12:39.926 --> 00:12:40.927
Ugh!

231
00:12:41.461 --> 00:12:42.462
Useless.

232
00:12:42.595 --> 00:12:47.271
You guys were incredible out there.
Especially you. Mr. Hat Trick.

233
00:12:47.367 --> 00:12:48.607
Oh. you're still here?

234
00:12:48.701 --> 00:12:50.476
Oh. you're still a jerk?

235
00:12:50.570 --> 00:12:51.742
Ooh! (CHUCKLES)

236
00:12:51.871 --> 00:12:52.872
Anyway

237
00:12:52.939 --> 00:12:54.782
I've been immersed in bending
my entire life.

238
00:12:54.874 --> 00:12:56.785
but I never learned
how to move like that.

239
00:12:56.876 --> 00:12:59.254
It's like there's a whole new style here.

240
00:12:59.312 --> 00:13:00.882
Think you could show me a few tricks?

241
00:13:00.947 --> 00:13:03.757
- Absolutely.
- MAKO: Right now?

242
00:13:04.384 --> 00:13:05.761
Come on. Bolin.

243
00:13:05.918 --> 00:13:07.056
Just ignore him.

244
00:13:07.120 --> 00:13:09.464
Yeah. I can show you the basics.

245
00:13:09.555 --> 00:13:12.968
I'm just not sure how my earthbending
would translate to your waterbending.

246
00:13:13.059 --> 00:13:14.436
but we'll figure it out.

247
00:13:14.627 --> 00:13:16.766
Won't be a problem.
I'm actually an Earthbender.

248
00:13:17.764 --> 00:13:19.937
I'm sorry!
No. no. I didn't mean to assume.

249
00:13:19.999 --> 00:13:23.310
'Cause. you know. I was just figuring
with your Water Tribe getup

250
00:13:23.403 --> 00:13:26.475
that you are a Water Tribe gal.

251
00:13:26.673 --> 00:13:29.984
No. you're right. I'm a Waterbender.
And a Firebender.

252
00:13:30.443 --> 00:13:31.786
Mmm. Mm-hmm.

253
00:13:32.345 --> 00:13:33.949
I'm very confused right now.

254
00:13:34.781 --> 00:13:37.125
You're the Avatar. and I'm an idiot.

255
00:13:37.183 --> 00:13:38.856
Both are true.

256
00:13:39.786 --> 00:13:41.788
No way.

257
00:13:41.921 --> 00:13:43.525
(WHISPERING LOUDLY) The Avatar!

258
00:13:44.791 --> 00:13:47.362
BOLIN: All right. let's see what you got.

259
00:13:51.164 --> 00:13:53.804
That was great! Good power.

260
00:13:53.800 --> 00:13:56.804
But in a real match
you'd be <i>a</i> sitting turtle-duck.

261
00:13:57.136 --> 00:13:58.638
Not so upright and flat-footed.

262
00:13:58.705 --> 00:14:00.013
Stay light on your toes.

263
00:14:00.106 --> 00:14:03.485
Right up until the moment
when you need to dig in and strike.

264
00:14:03.543 --> 00:14:04.954
Then. Pop! Pop!

265
00:14:08.314 --> 00:14:10.123
Okay. let me try it again.

266
00:14:14.821 --> 00:14:17.563
Wow! Nice adjustment.

267
00:14:17.657 --> 00:14:19.796
- You're a natural at this
- Not bad.

268
00:14:19.859 --> 00:14:21.839
What's it take to impress this guy?

269
00:14:21.828 --> 00:14:24.206
What? I said. "Not bad."

270
00:14:25.832 --> 00:14:27.311
You know what. it's getting late.

271
00:14:27.367 --> 00:14:28.903
I think I'm going to turn in.

272
00:14:29.001 --> 00:14:30.241
You kids have fun.

273
00:14:30.336 --> 00:14:33.340
Nice to meet you. Avatar Korra.

274
00:14:33.539 --> 00:14:35.485
Yeah. been a real pleasure.

275
00:14:35.541 --> 00:14:36.747
See you upstairs. bro.

276
00:14:36.843 --> 00:14:38.845
Upstairs? You guys live here?

277
00:14:38.845 --> 00:14:40.688
Yep. In the attic.

278
00:14:40.747 --> 00:14:43.353
It's nothing fancy.
but we have some great views.

279
00:14:43.416 --> 00:14:45.362
So back to bending.

280
00:14:45.418 --> 00:14:47.728
Why don't you throw that combo
one more time?

281
00:14:51.858 --> 00:14:53.064
(EXHALES)

282
00:14:55.728 --> 00:14:56.729
(GRUNTS)

283
00:14:58.865 --> 00:15:00.037
Patience. Korra.

284
00:15:09.876 --> 00:15:11.753
(PANTING)

285
00:15:13.246 --> 00:15:17.695
That was a 2000-year-old
historical treasure.

286
00:15:17.750 --> 00:15:20.287
What... What is wrong with you?

287
00:15:20.420 --> 00:15:21.865
There's nothing wrong with me!

288
00:15:21.921 --> 00:15:23.923
I've been practicing.
just like you taught me.

289
00:15:24.023 --> 00:15:26.367
But it isn't sinking in. okay?

290
00:15:26.426 --> 00:15:28.406
It hasn't "clicked" like you said it would.

291
00:15:28.628 --> 00:15:30.869
Korra. this isn't something
you can force.

292
00:15:30.930 --> 00:15:32.204
If you would only listen to me...

293
00:15:32.265 --> 00:15:34.245
I have been! But you know what I think?

294
00:15:34.300 --> 00:15:35.870
Maybe the problem isn't me.

295
00:15:35.935 --> 00:15:38.211
Maybe the reason
I haven't learned airbending yet

296
00:15:38.271 --> 00:15:40.911
is because you're a terrible teacher.

297
00:15:41.641 --> 00:15:42.642
(GROANS)

298
00:15:42.875 --> 00:15:44.946
Yeah. you're a terrible teacher. Daddy.

299
00:15:46.879 --> 00:15:47.949
Waa!

300
00:16:01.060 --> 00:16:02.835
Okay. everyone here?

301
00:16:03.095 --> 00:16:05.234
Wait. where's Korra?

302
00:16:05.631 --> 00:16:08.510
Honestly. Pema.
I am at my wit's end with that girl.

303
00:16:08.601 --> 00:16:10.478
I don't know how to get through to her!

304
00:16:11.938 --> 00:16:16.978
Dear. the best thing you can do right
now is to give Korra some space.

305
00:16:17.076 --> 00:16:19.955
You must promise me that
your teenage years won't be like this.

306
00:16:21.781 --> 00:16:23.818
I will make no such promises.

307
00:16:30.523 --> 00:16:32.298
I didn't miss your match. did I?

308
00:16:32.358 --> 00:16:33.962
You guys look like you lost already.

309
00:16:34.026 --> 00:16:35.334
We might as well have.

310
00:16:35.428 --> 00:16:37.499
Hasook's a no-good no-show!

311
00:16:38.297 --> 00:16:42.370
You got two minutes to come out
ready to play or you're disqualified.

312
00:16:42.468 --> 00:16:44.971
Well. there goes our shot
at the tournament.

313
00:16:44.971 --> 00:16:46.109
And the winnings.

314
00:16:46.339 --> 00:16:48.148
Can't you ask one of those guys
to fill in?

315
00:16:48.207 --> 00:16:51.518
No. the rules say you can only compete
on one team.

316
00:16:51.611 --> 00:16:53.989
Well. then how about me?

317
00:16:53.980 --> 00:16:56.984
I'm a top-notch Waterbender.
if I do say so myself.

318
00:16:57.049 --> 00:16:59.996
But you're the Avatar. Isn't that cheating?

319
00:16:59.986 --> 00:17:02.193
It isn't cheating if I only do waterbending.

320
00:17:02.288 --> 00:17:05.633
No way. I'd rather forfeit
than look like a fool out there.

321
00:17:05.725 --> 00:17:08.729
Wow. thanks for the vote of confidence.

322
00:17:08.828 --> 00:17:10.171
- Time's up. You in or out?
- We're in!

323
00:17:10.229 --> 00:17:11.333
- We are?
- Yes!

324
00:17:11.397 --> 00:17:12.501
Hey. I didn't agree to this...

325
00:17:12.565 --> 00:17:14.238
You can thank me later.

326
00:17:14.500 --> 00:17:16.070
This girl is crazy.

327
00:17:16.569 --> 00:17:18.742
<i>Looks like the Fire Ferrets
have ferreted out</i>

328
00:17:18.838 --> 00:17:20.647
<i>a last-minute replacement Waterbender.</i>

329
00:17:20.706 --> 00:17:22.413
<i>Let's see if she's another
diamond in the rough</i>

330
00:17:22.508 --> 00:17:24.920
<i>like the brothers
from the school of hard knocks.</i>

331
00:17:25.578 --> 00:17:28.024
Don't do anything too fancy
or aggressive.

332
00:17:28.014 --> 00:17:29.550
In fact. don't do anything.

333
00:17:29.649 --> 00:17:31.856
Just try not to get knocked off the ring.

334
00:17:31.918 --> 00:17:33.522
You got it. Captain.

335
00:17:35.021 --> 00:17:36.932
Players. are you ready?

336
00:17:37.023 --> 00:17:38.934
-(BLOWS WHISTLE)
-(BELL DINGS)

337
00:17:40.026 --> 00:17:41.027
(SCREAMS)

338
00:17:43.863 --> 00:17:44.898
Wahoo!

339
00:17:44.997 --> 00:17:46.032
- Man overboard!
-(WHISTLE BLOWS)

340
00:17:46.032 --> 00:17:50.037
Fire Ferret Waterbender. penalty!
Move back one zone!

341
00:17:50.102 --> 00:17:51.775
What? Why?

342
00:17:51.871 --> 00:17:56.047
You're only allowed lo knock players off
the back of the ring. not over the sides.

343
00:17:56.042 --> 00:17:57.680
Oh... Whoops.

344
00:17:58.711 --> 00:17:59.746
(BELL muss)

345
00:17:59.845 --> 00:18:02.052
<i>SHIRO: And we're
back in action after that hiccup.</i>

346
00:18:02.048 --> 00:18:05.393
<i>But I'm not so sure this replacement
player knows what she's doing.</i>

347
00:18:05.685 --> 00:18:06.720
(BUZZER SOUNDS)

348
00:18:06.786 --> 00:18:09.699
(BLOWS WHISTLE) Foul! Over the line.
Move back to Zone 3.

349
00:18:10.056 --> 00:18:12.058
(GRUNTS) I'll show you over the line...

350
00:18:13.192 --> 00:18:14.193
(BELL RINGS)

351
00:18:15.561 --> 00:18:18.041
<i>SHIRO: The Platypus Bears
take Round 1.</i>

352
00:18:18.097 --> 00:18:19.098
(BELL RINGS)

353
00:18:19.365 --> 00:18:21.971
<i>The Platypus Bears know
a green player when they see one.</i>

354
00:18:22.068 --> 00:18:26.210
<i>and they are focusing the brunt
of their bending on this poor girl.</i>

355
00:18:28.074 --> 00:18:29.075
(GROANS)

356
00:18:29.275 --> 00:18:32.279
<i>Wait a minute.
Did that Waterbender just earthbend?</i>

357
00:18:32.445 --> 00:18:33.446
(CROWD GASPS)

358
00:18:33.946 --> 00:18:34.947
(WHISTLE BLOWS)

359
00:18:35.081 --> 00:18:37.083
REF; Foul. I think.

360
00:18:37.450 --> 00:18:39.396
(LAUGHS NERVOUSLY)

361
00:18:39.952 --> 00:18:41.090
<i>- SHIRO: Did I see that right?
-(SIGHS)</i>

362
00:18:41.454 --> 00:18:44.765
<i>(OVER RADIO) Hold on. folks. we're just
waiting for the referee's official call.</i>

363
00:18:44.824 --> 00:18:47.100
<i>but I think this replacement player
could</i> be...

364
00:18:47.093 --> 00:18:50.097
Pardon me. everyone.
Have you seen Korra this evening?

365
00:18:50.096 --> 00:18:51.131
She's not in her room.

366
00:18:51.230 --> 00:18:52.641
<i>SHIRO: You've got to be kidding me.</i>

367
00:18:52.732 --> 00:18:54.575
<i>She's the Avatar. folks!</i>

368
00:18:54.634 --> 00:18:56.773
<i>Playing in a Pm-bending match!</i>

369
00:18:56.836 --> 00:18:58.509
<i>Can you believe that?</i>

370
00:18:58.604 --> 00:19:00.345
I'll get her myself.

371
00:19:02.475 --> 00:19:07.754
The Avatar will be permitted to continue
so long as she solely bends water.

372
00:19:07.947 --> 00:19:09.119
(PROTESTING)

373
00:19:10.116 --> 00:19:11.117
(BELL muss)

374
00:19:12.451 --> 00:19:15.022
<i>SHIRO: This girl may be the Avatar.
but she's no Pro-bender.</i>

375
00:19:15.121 --> 00:19:18.000
<i>And the Platypus Bears are
intent on exploiting that weakness.</i>

376
00:19:18.090 --> 00:19:21.196
<i>They're giving her their best and
her best ain't good enough to stop it!</i>

377
00:19:21.327 --> 00:19:24.206
<i>-(BUZZER SOUNDS)
- And she's in the drink!</i>

378
00:19:28.501 --> 00:19:30.037
(GRUNTING)

379
00:19:32.538 --> 00:19:34.313
KORRA: Oh. hey. Tenzin.

380
00:19:34.874 --> 00:19:37.150
I thought you didn't like
coming to these matches.

381
00:19:37.143 --> 00:19:38.144
(CHUCKLES)

382
00:19:38.210 --> 00:19:41.350
Once again. you have
flagrantly disobeyed my orders.

383
00:19:41.447 --> 00:19:44.053
You were to stay on the island. Let's go.

384
00:19:44.150 --> 00:19:46.221
No. I'm kind of
in the middle of something.

385
00:19:46.352 --> 00:19:50.664
I have tried my very best to get through
to you by being gentle and patient.

386
00:19:50.723 --> 00:19:53.727
But clearly the only thing
you respond to is force.

387
00:19:53.826 --> 00:19:56.363
So I am ordering you to come back
to the temple. Right now.

388
00:19:56.462 --> 00:20:01.172
Why? <i>So</i> I can sit around and meditate
about how bad I am at airbending?

389
00:20:01.167 --> 00:20:04.478
You know. I'm beginning to think there's
a reason I haven't been able to learn it.

390
00:20:04.537 --> 00:20:07.017
Because maybe I don't even need it.

391
00:20:07.073 --> 00:20:09.713
What? That is <i>a</i> ludicrous suggestion.

392
00:20:09.809 --> 00:20:13.052
The Avatar needs to learn airbending.
It is not optional.

393
00:20:13.179 --> 00:20:17.184
No. This is what I need to learn.
Modern styles of fighting.

394
00:20:17.183 --> 00:20:20.187
Being the Avatar isn't
all about fighting. Korra.

395
00:20:20.252 --> 00:20:21.890
When will you learn that?

396
00:20:21.987 --> 00:20:23.762
I have a match to go finish.

397
00:20:23.856 --> 00:20:24.857
(BELL muss)

398
00:20:24.990 --> 00:20:28.870
<i>RING ANNOUNCER:
The Platypus Bears win Round 2.</i>

399
00:20:28.928 --> 00:20:30.271
<i>Round 3!</i>

400
00:20:35.668 --> 00:20:37.204
<i>SHIRO: The Platypus Bears
come out of the gate</i>

401
00:20:37.203 --> 00:20:39.183
<i>and quickly go after the Ferret brothers.</i>

402
00:20:39.238 --> 00:20:42.219
<i>They're corralled in the comer.
wedged in the edge of Zone 1.</i>

403
00:20:42.208 --> 00:20:44.210
<i>unable to come to the Avatar's rescue.</i>

404
00:20:44.210 --> 00:20:46.212
<i>And. boy. does she need it!</i>

405
00:20:47.346 --> 00:20:49.189
(CHEERING)

406
00:20:51.751 --> 00:20:55.563
<i>Looks like the Avatar's Pro-bending
debut is going to be cut short.</i>

407
00:20:55.955 --> 00:20:59.732
<i>She's been pushed back to Zone 3
and the water is calling her name.</i>

408
00:20:59.892 --> 00:21:02.099
<i>It's only a matter of time before...</i>

409
00:21:02.194 --> 00:21:05.403
<i>Hold the phone. stop the presses.
She's still in the game. folks!</i>

410
00:21:05.531 --> 00:21:07.738
<i>And she's moving like an entirely
different player!</i>

411
00:21:07.800 --> 00:21:12.249
<i>All of a sudden the Platypus Bears'
strikes are only striking air!</i>

412
00:21:13.239 --> 00:21:14.980
How about that?

413
00:21:17.042 --> 00:21:19.113
<i>The Platypus Bears have no juice left.</i>

414
00:21:19.211 --> 00:21:21.714
<i>but Mako and Bolin are
still fresh and juicy.</i>

415
00:21:31.924 --> 00:21:33.062
(GRUNTS)

416
00:21:35.928 --> 00:21:36.929
(BUZZER SOUNDS)

417
00:21:39.331 --> 00:21:40.332
(BUZZER SOUNDS)

418
00:21:43.669 --> 00:21:44.670
(BUZZER SOUNDS)

419
00:21:45.671 --> 00:21:47.275
-(BELL DINGS)
- Knockout!

420
00:21:47.273 --> 00:21:48.274
(HOOTING IN CELEBRATION)

421
00:21:48.340 --> 00:21:51.753
<i>SHIRO: The Fire Ferrets come
from way behind and steal the win.</i>

422
00:21:51.811 --> 00:21:53.085
<i>What an upset. folks.</i>

423
00:21:53.145 --> 00:21:54.988
<i>The rookies. Avatar in tow.</i>

424
00:21:55.080 --> 00:21:57.686
<i>have nabbed a place
in the Championship Tournament!</i>

425
00:21:57.817 --> 00:21:59.797
<i>I cannot believe it.</i>

426
00:22:01.153 --> 00:22:02.257
(BOTH LAUGHING)

427
00:22:02.321 --> 00:22:03.698
- Yeah.
- Yes!

428
00:22:04.423 --> 00:22:06.801
Korra. what can I say?

429
00:22:06.859 --> 00:22:09.271
You really came alive in that last round.

430
00:22:09.328 --> 00:22:12.309
The way you dodged their attacks.
You are a natural.

431
00:22:12.298 --> 00:22:15.279
Thanks. but I can't take all the credit.

432
00:22:15.334 --> 00:22:17.439
Someone else taught me those moves.

433
00:22:25.377 --> 00:22:29.325
I'm really sorry about everything I said.

434
00:22:29.315 --> 00:22:33.195
I was really frustrated with myself
and I took it out on you.

435
00:22:33.319 --> 00:22:35.390
I think I owe you an apology. too.

436
00:22:35.487 --> 00:22:39.401
I was trying to teach you about patience.
but I lost mine.

437
00:22:39.525 --> 00:22:40.629
No hard feelings?

438
00:22:40.860 --> 00:22:42.464
Of course not.

439
00:22:42.561 --> 00:22:45.041
By the way'
you were really good out there tonight.

440
00:22:45.130 --> 00:22:47.076
You moved just like an Airbender.

441
00:22:47.166 --> 00:22:49.339
Wait. you stayed and watched?

442
00:22:49.335 --> 00:22:53.340
I did. Pro-bending turned out to be
the perfect teaching tool for you.

443
00:22:56.809 --> 00:23:00.086
I'll see you tomorrow
for airbending practice. bright and early!

444
00:23:00.179 --> 00:23:03.023
And by the way. I kind of
permanently joined the Fire Ferrets

445
00:23:03.082 --> 00:23:05.392
and we're playing in the tournament
in a couple of weeks.

446
00:23:05.484 --> 00:23:06.485
(SIGHS)
